  "instructions": [
    "Cut the lamb into 1-inch cubes and thread onto the bamboo skewers, leaving a little space between each piece.",
    "In a medium bowl, whisk together the gochujang, soy sauce, rice vinegar, sesame oil, honey, garlic, ginger, green onions, sesame seeds, salt, black pepper, sugar, yuzu juice, sushi rice vinegar, miso paste, and chili flakes until smooth.",
    "Add the cornstarch and water to the bowl and whisk until the mixture is free of lumps.",
    "Brush the lamb skewers with the soy sauce mixture and coat evenly.",
    "Let the skewers marinate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours in the refrigerator.",
    "Preheat the grill to medium-high heat and cook the skewers for 4-6 minutes per side, or until they are nicely charred and cooked through.",
    "Transfer the skewers to a plate and garnish with scallions and yuzu zest.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
